the chairperson or a person entering a place under section 44 of this act may enter using reasonable force and without a warrant or the consent of the owner or occupant of the place, provided that the person makes a reasonable attempt to do the following:
* inform the owner or occupant the purpose of the entry;
* inform the owner or occupant that it is permitted under this Act to enter the place without the owner or occupantâs consent.
* search any part of the place;
* open a container or other item at the place using reasonable force;
* remove any item from the place;

